ZH: 铁是一种金属。
EN: Iron is a type of metal.

ZH: 这条链子是铁制的。
EN: This chain is made of iron.

ZH: 铁锅是我家用的最多的锅。
EN: The iron pot is the most frequently used pot in my house.

ZH: 她用铁丝做了一个漂亮的手镯。
EN: She made a beautiful bracelet with iron wire.

ZH: 这座桥是用铁铸成的。
EN: This bridge is cast in iron.

ZH: 现在很少有铁路公司在运营着。
EN: There are few railway companies operating nowadays.

ZH: 这个工厂是专门生产铁器的。
EN: This factory specializes in producing ironware.

ZH: 这把椅子腿是纯铁铸造的。
EN: The legs of this chair are cast in pure iron.

ZH: 铁路是很方便的交通工具。
EN: Railways are very convenient means of transportation.

ZH: 铁杆是很坚固的。
EN: Iron bars are very strong.

ZH: 铁钉在锁门时很有用。
EN: Iron nails are useful for locking doors.

ZH: 铁炮已经过时了。
EN: Iron cannons are now outdated.

ZH: 铁环上系着一张网。
EN: A net is tied to the iron ring.

ZH: 铁链子绑住了那只野兽。
EN: The wild beast is bound by an iron chain.

ZH: 铁锅炖的排骨味道很好。
EN: The ribs stewed in the iron pot taste delicious.

ZH: 铁匠正在打铁。
EN: The blacksmith is hammering iron.

ZH: 铁手铐用来束缚罪犯。
EN: Iron handcuffs are used to restrain criminals.

ZH: 铁链拴住了船只。
EN: The boat is tied up by an iron chain.

ZH: 铁是我们生活中很重要的材料之一。
EN: Iron is one of the most important materials in our daily life.

ZH: 昨天我用铁切了一块砖。
EN: Yesterday, I cut a brick with iron.
